Apple Inc Pays $60 Million To Settle China iPad Trademark Dispute With Unit Of Proview International Holdings Limited-Reuters
Monday, 2 Jul 2012 01:00am EDT
Reuters reported that Apple Inc has paid $60 million to Proview Technology (Shenzhen) to end a dispute over the iPad trademark in China that saw the company engaged in a protracted legal tussle with a near-bankrupt Chinese firm. The lawsuit had hampered some sales and delayed the launch of the new iPad in China. Prior to the launch. The court-mediated settlement, announced on the website of the Higher People's Court of Guangdong province, will allow Apple to get on with selling its popular tablet PC in one of its most important markets. Apple and Proview Technology (Shenzhen), a unit of Proview International Holdings Limited, have been negotiating to reach a settlement since the court conducted an initial hearing in February, after Apple appealed a lower court ruling against it.Â 
